1 Section 3-8-102. A. As used in the Terry Peach North Canadian
2 Watershed Water Restoration Act:
3 1. “Commission” means the Oklahoma Conservation Commission;
4 2. “Harmful woody species” means a tree or shrub species that
5 is rapidly encroaching into adjoining lands and is likely to cause
6 harm to the environment or economy. Harmful woody species include,
7 but are not limited to, Juniperus virginiana (Eastern Redcedar),
8 Juniperus scopulorum (Rocky Mountain juniper), Juniperus monosperma
9 (oneseed juniper) and, Tamarix ramosissima (salt cedar), Juniperus
10 pinchotii (redberry juniper), Juniper ashei (ashe juniper), and
11 Prosopis glandulosa (honey mesquite); and
12 3. “North Canadian Watershed” means the an area of land in
13 Oklahoma that drains or sheds water into the North Canadian River a
14 waterway or water basin.
15 B. There Subject to the availability of funds, there is hereby
16 created a statewide pilot program to remove or eradicate harmful
17 woody species in the North Canadian Watershed watersheds to be
18 administered by through the Oklahoma Conservation Commission. To
19 accomplish the goals listed in this section, the Commission is
20 authorized to use the funds available in the North Canadian
21 Watershed Water Restoration Revolving Fund established in Section 3
22 of this act 3-8-103 of this title. The purpose of the program is to
23 manage and eradicate, where possible, harmful woody species that
24 damage grazing lands, create significant wildfire risk, reduce
